- The target image shows a red rectangular block with a circular hole/tunnel running through its center.
- The structure appears to be made of 4 identical parts that connect to form the complete shape.
- There are 2 layers (top and bottom) with 2 blocks in each layer.

## Spatial Relationships:
- The structure has a symmetrical design with matching top and bottom halves.
- Each block forms one quarter of the structure, with the circular cutouts aligning perfectly to create the tunnel.
- The blocks are arranged in a 2Ã—2 configuration when viewed from the front.

## Required Blocks Selection:
Looking at the block dictionary, I can see that I need blocks that will form the corners of the structure with appropriate circular cutouts. Based on careful examination of the orientations:

- Block #1: Forms the top-left quarter
- Block #2: Forms the top-right quarter
- Block #1: Forms the bottom-left quarter (reusing the same block)
- Block #2: Forms the bottom-right quarter (reusing the same block)

## Assembly Order:
```
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1
    Step2: Move block with index 2
    Step3: Move block with index 1
    Step4: Move block with index 2
}
```

The assembly would start with the bottom layer (blocks 1 and 2) and then add the top layer (another set of blocks 1 and 2) to complete the structure with the circular hole running through it.
